${project.name} Architecture Notes
==============================

${project.name} connects to an [AMQP](https://www.amqp.org/) provider using the [protonj2 client](https://qpid.apache.org/proton/index.html) from the  [Apache QPID](https://qpid.apache.org/) ) messaging library to read AMQP messages. It utilizes the [Aiven Kafka Connector Framework](https://github.com/Aiven-Open/aiven-kafka-connector-framework) to do most of the heavy lifting.

The AMQP message provider contract does not require that a message have a unique key, the connector framework expects that each message will have a unique ID and that those IDs can be lexically ordered.  The framework calls these IDs NativeKeys.  To meet the native key requirement we assign every message that arrives in the system a [ULID](https://github.com/ulid/spec). We use the [Sulky java implementation of ULID](https://github.com/huxi/sulky/blob/27c8d809f2e3af6eafa9c7324f158cd9b482b351/sulky-ulid/README.md) from [Jörn Huxhorn](https://github.com/huxi).

Each message is parsed into a JSON document that contains all the components of the message.  Each AMQP message creates one Kafka message.  The extraction of the kafka message body from the AMQP message occurs in the AmqpExtractor class.





